  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Sorrow in Jerusalem
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]  Jerusalem, once so full of people,is now deserted.She
        who was once great among the nationsnow sits alone like a widow.Once the
        queen of all the earth,she is now a slave.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1 '
        content: '  Each of the first four chapters of this book is an acrostic,
          laid out in the order of the Hebrew alphabet. The first word of each verse
          begins with a successive Hebrew letter. Chapters 1, 2, and 4 have one verse
          for each of the 22 Hebrew letters. Chapter 3 contains 22 stanzas of three
          verses each. Though chapter 5 has 22 verses, it is not an acrostic.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'She sobs through the night;tears stream down her cheeks.Among all
        her lovers,there is no one left to comfort her.All her friends have betrayed
        herand become her enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Judah has been led away into captivity,oppressed with cruel slavery.She
        lives among foreign nationsand has no place of rest.Her enemies have chased
        her down,and she has nowhere to turn.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The roads to Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] are in mourning,for crowds no
        longer come to celebrate the festivals.The city gates are silent,her priests
        groan,her young women are crying\u2014how bitter is her fate!  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion; </b>also in 1:17.
    - title: 
      content: 'Her oppressors have become her masters,and her enemies prosper,for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has punished Jerusalemfor her many sins.Her
        children have been capturedand taken away to distant lands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All the majesty of beautiful Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]has been stripped
        away.Her princes are like starving deersearching for pasture.They are too
        weak to runfrom the pursuing enemy.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of the daughter of Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'In the midst of her sadness and wandering,Jerusalem remembers her
        ancient splendor.But now she has fallen to her enemy,and there is no one
        to help her.Her enemy struck her downand laughed as she fell.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jerusalem has sinned greatly,so she has been tossed away like a filthy
        rag.All who once honored her now despise her,for they have seen her stripped
        naked and humiliated.All she can do is groanand hide her face.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She defiled herself with immoralityand gave no thought to her future.Now
        she lies in the gutterwith no one to lift her out.\u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        see my misery,\u201D she cries.\u201CThe enemy has triumphed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The enemy has plundered her completely,taking every precious thing
        she owns.She has seen foreigners violate her sacred Temple,the place the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had forbidden them to enter.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Her people groan as they search for bread.They have sold their treasures
        for food to stay alive.\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, look,\u201D she
        mourns,\u201Cand see how I am despised.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDoes it mean nothing to you, all you who pass by?Look around
        and see if there is any suffering like mine,which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        brought on mewhen he erupted in fierce anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHe has sent fire from heaven that burns in my bones.He has
        placed a trap in my path and turned me back.He has left me devastated,racked
        with sickness all day long.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHe wove my sins into ropesto hitch me to a yoke of captivity.The
        Lord sapped my strength and turned me over to my enemies;I am helpless in
        their hands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe Lord has treated my mighty menwith contempt.At his command
        a great army has cometo crush my young warriors.The Lord has trampled his
        beloved city[[COMMENT(0)]]like grapes are trampled in a winepress.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the virgin daughter of Judah.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor all these things I weep;tears flow down my cheeks.No one
        is here to comfort me;any who might encourage me are far away.My children
        have no future,for the enemy has conquered us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jerusalem reaches out for help,but no one comforts her.Regarding
        his people Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has said,\u201CLet
        their neighbors be their enemies!Let them be thrown away like a filthy rag!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:17 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Jacob. </b>The names \u201CJacob\u201D and \u201CIsrael\u201D
          are often interchanged throughout the Old Testament, referring sometimes
          to the individual patriarch and sometimes to the nation."
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is right,\u201D Jerusalem says,\u201Cfor
        I rebelled against him.Listen, people everywhere;look upon my anguish and
        despair,for my sons and daughtershave been taken captive to distant lands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI begged my allies for help,but they betrayed me.My priests
        and leadersstarved to death in the city,even as they searched for foodto
        save their lives.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, see my anguish!My heart is brokenand
        my soul despairs,for I have rebelled against you.In the streets the sword
        kills,and at home there is only death.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COthers heard my groans,but no one turned to comfort me.When
        my enemies heard about my troubles,they were happy to see what you had done.Oh,
        bring the day you promised,when they will suffer as I have suffered.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "God\u2019s Anger at Sin"
      content: "  The Lord in his angerhas cast a dark shadow over beautiful Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]The
        fairest of Israel\u2019s cities lies in the dust,thrown down from the heights
        of heaven.In his day of great anger,the Lord has shown no mercy even to his
        Temple.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1a '
        content: Hebrew <b>the daughter of Zion; </b>also in 2:8, 10, 18.
      - number: '2:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>his footstool.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Without mercy the Lord has destroyedevery home in Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]In
        his anger he has broken downthe fortress walls of beautiful Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(1)]]He
        has brought them to the ground,dishonoring the kingdom and its rulers.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:2a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jacob; </b>also in 2:3b. See note on 1:17.
      - number: '2:2b '
        content: Hebrew <b>the daughter of Judah; </b>also in 2:5.
    - title: 
      content: 'All the strength of Israelvanishes beneath his fierce anger.The Lord
        has withdrawn his protectionas the enemy attacks.He consumes the whole land
        of Israellike a raging fire.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He bends his bow against his people,as though he were their enemy.His
        strength is used against themto kill their finest youth.His fury is poured
        out like fireon beautiful Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>on the tent of the daughter of Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, the Lord has vanquished Israellike an enemy.He has destroyed
        her palacesand demolished her fortresses.He has brought unending sorrow and
        tearsupon beautiful Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has broken down his Templeas though it were merely a garden shelter.The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has blotted out all memoryof the holy festivals
        and Sabbath days.Kings and priests fall togetherbefore his fierce anger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Lord has rejected his own altar;he despises his own sanctuary.He
        has given Jerusalem\u2019s palacesto her enemies.They shout in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Templeas though it were a day of celebration.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was determinedto destroy the walls
        of beautiful Jerusalem.He made careful plans for their destruction,then did
        what he had planned.Therefore, the ramparts and wallshave fallen down before
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jerusalem\u2019s gates have sunk into the ground.He has smashed their
        locks and bars.Her kings and princes have been exiled to distant lands;her
        law has ceased to exist.Her prophets receiveno more visions from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The leaders of beautiful Jerusalemsit on the ground in silence.They
        are clothed in burlapand throw dust on their heads.The young women of Jerusalemhang
        their heads in shame.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have cried until the tears no longer come;my heart is broken.My
        spirit is poured out in agonyas I see the desperate plight of my people.Little
        children and tiny babiesare fainting and dying in the streets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They cry out to their mothers,\u201CWe need food and drink!\u201DTheir
        lives ebb away in the streetslike the life of a warrior wounded in battle.They
        gasp for lifeas they collapse in their mothers\u2019 arms.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What can I say about you?Who has ever seen such sorrow?O daughter
        of Jerusalem,to what can I compare your anguish?O virgin daughter of Zion,how
        can I comfort you?For your wound is as deep as the sea.Who can heal you?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your prophets have saidso many foolish things, false to the core.They
        did not save you from exileby pointing out your sins.Instead, they painted
        false pictures,filling you with false hope.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All who pass by jeer at you.They scoff and insult beautiful Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        saying,\u201CIs this the city called \u2018Most Beautiful in All the World\u2019and
        \u2018Joy of All the Earth\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the daughter of Jerusalem.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "All your enemies mock you.They scoff and snarl and say,\u201CWe have
        destroyed her at last!We have long waited for this day,and it is finally
        here!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But it is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who did just as he planned.He
        has fulfilled the promises of disasterhe made long ago.He has destroyed Jerusalem
        without mercy.He has caused her enemies to gloat over herand has given them
        power over her.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Cry aloud[[COMMENT(0)]] before the Lord,O walls of beautiful Jerusalem!Let
        your tears flow like a riverday and night.Give yourselves no rest;give your
        eyes no relief.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Their heart cried.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Rise during the night and cry out.Pour out your hearts like water
        to the Lord.Lift up your hands to him in prayer,pleading for your children,for
        in every streetthey are faint with hunger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, think about this!Should you
        treat your own people this way?Should mothers eat their own children,those
        they once bounced on their knees?Should priests and prophets be killedwithin
        the Lord\u2019s Temple?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSee them lying in the streets\u2014young and old,boys and girls,killed
        by the swords of the enemy.You have killed them in your anger,slaughtering
        them without mercy.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Hope in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Faithfulness"
      content: "  I am the one who has seen the afflictionsthat come from the rod
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has led me into darkness,shutting out all light.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has turned his hand against meagain and again, all day long.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has made my skin and flesh grow old.He has broken my bones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has besieged and surrounded mewith anguish and distress.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has buried me in a dark place,like those long dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has walled me in, and I cannot escape.He has bound me in heavy
        chains.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And though I cry and shout,he has shut out my prayers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has blocked my way with a high stone wall;he has made my road
        crooked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has hidden like a bear or a lion,waiting to attack me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has dragged me off the path and torn me in pieces,leaving me helpless
        and devastated.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has drawn his bowand made me the target for his arrows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He shot his arrowsdeep into my heart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My own people laugh at me.All day long they sing their mocking songs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has filled me with bitternessand given me a bitter cup of sorrow
        to drink.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has made me chew on gravel.He has rolled me in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Peace has been stripped away,and I have forgotten what prosperity
        is.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I cry out, \u201CMy splendor is gone!Everything I had hoped for from
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is lost!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The thought of my suffering and homelessnessis bitter beyond words.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:19 '
        content: Or <b>is wormwood and gall.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I will never forget this awful time,as I grieve over my loss.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet I still dare to hopewhen I remember this:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The faithful love of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> never ends![[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>His
        mercies never cease.</smallcaps>  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:22 '
        content: As in Syriac version; Hebrew reads <b>of the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>
          keeps us from destruction.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Great is his faithfulness;his mercies begin afresh each morning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I say to myself, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is my inheritance;therefore,
        I will hope in him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is good to those who depend on him,to
        those who search for him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So it is good to wait quietlyfor salvation from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And it is good for people to submit at an early ageto the yoke of
        his discipline:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let them sit alone in silencebeneath the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        demands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them lie face down in the dust,for there may be hope at last.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them turn the other cheek to those who strike themand accept
        the insults of their enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For no one is abandonedby the Lord forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though he brings grief, he also shows compassionbecause of the greatness
        of his unfailing love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he does not enjoy hurting peopleor causing them sorrow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If people crush underfootall the prisoners of the land,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'if they deprive others of their rightsin defiance of the Most High,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "if they twist justice in the courts\u2014doesn\u2019t the Lord see
        all these things?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who can command things to happenwithout the Lord\u2019s permission?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Does not the Most Highsend both calamity and good?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then why should we, mere humans, complainwhen we are punished for
        our sins?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, let us test and examine our ways.Let us turn back to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let us lift our hearts and handsto God in heaven and say,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWe have sinned and rebelled,and you have not forgiven us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou have engulfed us with your anger, chased us down,and slaughtered
        us without mercy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have hidden yourself in a cloudso our prayers cannot reach you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have discarded us as refuse and garbageamong the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll our enemieshave spoken out against us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We are filled with fear,for we are trapped, devastated, and ruined.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Tears stream from my eyesbecause of the destruction of my people!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My tears flow endlessly;they will not stop  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'until the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> looks downfrom heaven and sees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My heart is breakingover the fate of all the women of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies, whom I have never harmed,hunted me down like a bird.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They threw me into a pitand dropped stones on me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The water rose over my head,and I cried out, \u201CThis is the end!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I called on your name, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,from deep
        within the pit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You heard me when I cried, \u201CListen to my pleading!Hear my cry
        for help!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, you came when I called;you told me, \u201CDo not fear.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lord, you have come to my defense;you have redeemed my life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have seen the wrong they have done to me, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Be
        my judge, and prove me right.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have seen the vengeful plotsmy enemies have laid against me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you have heard the vile names they
        call me.You know all about the plans they have made.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies whisper and mutteras they plot against me all day long.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look at them! Whether they sit or stand,I am the object of their
        mocking songs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pay them back, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for all the evil they
        have done.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give them hard and stubborn hearts,and then let your curse fall on
        them!  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "God\u2019s Anger Satisfied"
      content: '  How the gold has lost its luster!Even the finest gold has become
        dull.The sacred gemstoneslie scattered in the streets!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See how the precious children of Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]worth their
        weight in fine gold,are now treated like pots of claymade by a common potter.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>precious sons of Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Even the jackals feed their young,but not my people Israel.They ignore
        their children\u2019s cries,like ostriches in the desert.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The parched tongues of their little onesstick to the roofs of their
        mouths in thirst.The children cry for bread,but no one has any to give them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people who once ate the richest foodsnow beg in the streets for
        anything they can get.Those who once wore the finest clothesnow search the
        garbage dumps for food.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The guilt[[COMMENT(0)]] of my peopleis greater than that of Sodom,where
        utter disaster struck in a momentand no hand offered help.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        content: Or <b>punishment.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Our princes once glowed with health\u2014brighter than snow, whiter
        than milk.Their faces were as ruddy as rubies,their appearance like fine
        jewels.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>like lapis lazuli.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But now their faces are blacker than soot.No one recognizes them
        in the streets.Their skin sticks to their bones;it is as dry and hard as
        wood.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those killed by the sword are better offthan those who die of hunger.Starving,
        they waste awayfor lack of food from the fields.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Tenderhearted womenhave cooked their own children.They have eaten
        themto survive the siege.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is satisfied.His
        fierce anger has been poured out.He started a fire in Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]that
        burned the city to its foundations.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Not a king in all the earth\u2014no one in all the world\u2014would
        have believed that an enemycould march through the gates of Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet it happened because of the sins of her prophetsand the sins of
        her priests,who defiled the cityby shedding innocent blood.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They wandered blindlythrough the streets,so defiled by bloodthat
        no one dared touch them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGet away!\u201D the people shouted at them.\u201CYou\u2019re
        defiled! Don\u2019t touch us!\u201DSo they fled to distant landsand wandered
        among foreign nations,but none would let them stay.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>himself has scattered them,and he
        no longer helps them.People show no respect for the priestsand no longer
        honor the leaders.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We looked in vain for our alliesto come and save us,but we were looking
        to nationsthat could not help us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We couldn\u2019t go into the streetswithout danger to our lives.Our
        end was near; our days were numbered.We were doomed!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our enemies were swifter than eagles in flight.If we fled to the
        mountains, they found us.If we hid in the wilderness,they were waiting for
        us there.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Our king\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anointed, the
        very life of our nation\u2014was caught in their snares.We had thought that
        his shadowwould protect us against any nation on earth!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Are you rejoicing in the land of Uz,O people of Edom?But you, too,
        must drink from the cup of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger.You,
        too, will be stripped naked in your drunkenness.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Prayer for Restoration
      content: '    <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, remember what has happened to us.See
        how we have been disgraced!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our inheritance has been turned over to strangers,our homes to foreigners.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are orphaned and fatherless.Our mothers are widowed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We have to pay for water to drink,and even firewood is expensive.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who pursue us are at our heels;we are exhausted but are given
        no rest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We submitted to Egypt and Assyriato get enough food to survive.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Our ancestors sinned, but they have died\u2014and we are suffering
        the punishment they deserved!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Slaves have now become our masters;there is no one left to rescue
        us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We hunt for food at the risk of our lives,for violence rules the
        countryside.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The famine has blackened our skinas though baked in an oven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our enemies rape the women in Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]and the young
        girls in all the towns of Judah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Our princes are being hanged by their thumbs,and our elders are treated
        with contempt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Young men are led away to work at millstones,and boys stagger under
        heavy loads of wood.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The elders no longer sit in the city gates;the young men no longer
        dance and sing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Joy has left our hearts;our dancing has turned to mourning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The garlands have[[COMMENT(0)]] fallen from our heads.Weep for us
        because we have sinned.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:16 '
        content: Or <b>The crown has.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Our hearts are sick and weary,and our eyes grow dim with tears.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] is empty and desolate,a place haunted
        by jackals.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Mount Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you remain the same forever!Your
        throne continues from generation to generation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why do you continue to forget us?Why have you abandoned us for so
        long?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Restore us, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and bring us back to you
        again!Give us back the joys we once had!  '
      comments: []
